title: Malaysia overtakes Indonesia
text:
Saturday, 4 February 2017 Malaysia overtakes Indonesia 
TELUK INTAN: Malaysia has overtaken Indonesia as the biggest exporter of crude palm oil to China. 
Plantation Industries and Com­­modities Minister Datuk Seri Mah Siew Keong, who disclosed this, said that Datuk Seri Najib Tun Razak’s visit to China last November made this possible. 
He said Malaysia exported 993.9 thousand metric tonnes of crude palm oil to China from July to De­­cember last year. 
“This is a 53.6% increase over that period, while Indonesia’s export performance dropped 21%. 
“Six years ago we were the biggest palm oil exporters to China until Indonesia overtook us early last year,’’ he told reporters after accompanying Chinese Embassy minister counsellor Ma Jia on a visit to the clock tower here yesterday. 
Ma Jia said she hoped Malaysia would continue to be the main exporter of crude palm oil to China. 
“China is always interested to do business with Malaysia. We have always had good bilateral re­­lations and it will continue for many more years to come,” she said.
